

The format for running the @command{vguitar} program is:

@example
vguitar @var{option} @dots{}
@end example

@command{vguitar} supports the following options:

@table @option

@item --tablature
@itemx -t

@item --strum
@itemx -s

@item --clip
@itemx -c

@item --input=@var{text}
@itemx -i

@item --output=@var{text}
@itemx -o

@item --allput=@var{text}
@itemx -u

@item --addr=@var{server_add}
@itemx -A 

@item --port=@var{server_port}
@itemx -P

@item --bpm=@var{beats per minute}
@itemx -b

@item --roll=@var{roll factor}
@itemx -r

@item --version
@itemx -v
Print the version number and licensing information of Vguitar on
standard output and then exit successfully.

@end table
